{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"110103","heading":"Purposes","label":"110103 Purposes","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/stII/ptB/ch1101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Historical and Revision NotesRevisedSectionSource (U.S. Code)Source (Statutes at Large)11010336:2703., , .Aug. 21, 1984Pub. L. 98–391, § 398 Stat. 1358Before clause (1), the word “objects” is omitted as included in “purposes”."],"amendments":["Historical and Revision NotesRevisedSectionSource (U.S. Code)Source (Statutes at Large)11010336:2703., , .Aug. 21, 1984Pub. L. 98–391, § 398 Stat. 1358Before clause (1), the word “objects” is omitted as included in “purposes”."],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"maintain true allegiance to the United States;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"foster and perpetuate true Americanism;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"combat whatever tends to impair the efficiency and permanency of our free institutions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"uphold the fair name of Jews and fight their battles wherever unjustly assailed;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"encourage the doctrine of universal liberty, equal rights, and full justice to all men;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"combat the powers of bigotry and darkness wherever originating and whatever the target;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"preserve the spirit of comradeship by mutual helpfulness to comrades and their families;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"cooperate with and support existing educational institutions and establish educational institutions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"foster the education of ex-servicemen and ex-servicewomen and members of the corporation in the ideals and principles of Americanism;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"instill love of country and flag;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":null,"label":"11","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"promote sound minds and bodies in members of the corporation and their youth;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"12","heading":null,"label":"12","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/12","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F12","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"preserve the memories and records of patriotic service performed by the men and women of the Jewish faith and honor their memory; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"13","heading":null,"label":"13","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103/13","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s110103","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs110103%2F13","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shield from neglect the graves of our heroic dead.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
